FBIS3-41258 "jptdd007__l94048" JPRS-TDD-94-007-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 14 February 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA EGYPT 8 Kg of Crude Opium Oil Found in Vehicle Driven From Libya NC1102114394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2150 GMT 10 Feb 94 NC1102114394 Cairo MENA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Al-Sallum, 10 Feb (MENA)--Undercover agents at the al-Sallum border crossing today seized 8 kg of crude opium oil [Zayt al-Afyun al-Kham] in bottles concealed inside the tires of a vehicle driving from Libya. The driver, Hafiz 'Abd-al-Sattar Muhammad, said he is employed by Ayman Khidr, the proprietor of an import-export firm in Alexandria. He added that he took delivery of the vehicle from its owner in the Libyan town of Darnah. The owner told him he would follow him in three days. Sa'd Mutawalli, chief prosecutor in Marsa Matruh Governorate, remanded the driver for four days pending investigation and sent a specimen of the seized merchandise to the forensic laboratory for examination. He also issued instructions to arraign the export firm proprietor.
